Then(/^I tear down the "([^\"]*)" project using JSON$/) do |access_name|
    json_req('Get', "#{$testray_path}/projects/_#{CGI::escape(access_name)}.json", {})
    unless @hash_response['status'] == 400
        projectid = @hash_response['data']['testrayProjectId']
        json_delete_project("#{projectid}")
    end
end

Then(/^I add the "([^\"]*)" component to the "([^\"]*)" team using JSON$/) do |component_name, team_name|
	testray_get(team_name, 'teams', uri_param: "?testrayProjectId=#{@projectid}")
	@teamid = get_hash_response('teams', team_name)

	json_req('Post', "#{$testray_path}/components.json", {testrayProjectId: "#{@projectid}", name: "#{component_name}", testrayTeamId: "#{@teamid}"}, expected_status: 200)
	@componentid = get_hash_response('components', component_name)
end

	Capybara.current_driver = :selenium_chrome
	Capybara.app_host = ("#{$protocol}://#{$testray_instance}/web/guest/home")
	dest_url = "#{$protocol}://#{$testray_instance}/web/guest/home?p_p_id=com_liferay_login_web_portlet_LoginPortlet&p_p_lifecycle=0&p_p_state=maximized&p_p_mode=view&saveLastPath=false&_com_liferay_login_web_portlet_LoginPortlet_mvcRenderCommandName=%2Flogin%2Flogin"
	
	visit(dest_url)
	attempts = 1
	unless assert_current_path(dest_url, {url: true, wait: 3})
		if attempts >= 5
			break
		else
			visit(dest_url)
			puts "Browser failed to open. On attempt: " + attempts.to_s
			attempts += 1
		end
	end

	using_wait_time 120 do # Ensure that the page actually loads before proceding
		step "I should see the \"Sign In\" button on the page"
	end

	Capybara.page.current_window.resize_to(1920, 1080)

	step "I enter \"#{access_name}\" into the \"Email Address\" input field"
	step "I enter \"testray\" into the \"Password\" input field"
	check('_com_liferay_login_web_portlet_LoginPortlet_rememberMe')

	using_wait_time 360 do
		step "I click the \"Sign In\" button"
	end

	# using_wait_time 60 do
	# 	step "I select the \"Project Directory\" option from the project global drop down"
	# end

	switch_to_main_content
end

Then(/^I set the following default environment factors on the "([^\"]*)" routine in the "([^\"]*)" project using JSON$/) do |job_name, project_name, table|
	factor_arr = []
	table.rows.each do |category_name, option_name|
		testray_factors = {
			  'testrayFactorOptionName' => "#{option_name}",
			  'testrayFactorCategoryName' => "#{category_name}"
		}
		factor_arr.push(testray_factors)
	end

	testray_data = {
		  defaultTestrayFactors: "#{factor_arr}"
	}
	$master_map['routines'][job_name].set_default_factors(factor_arr)
	$master_map['routines'][job_name].update(testray_data)
end

	thread_lim = 200
	threads = []
	$master_map['builds'] ||= {}

    if try.empty?
	    table.rows.each do |job_name, build_name, build_desc, product_version|
		    until threads.map { |t| t.status }.count('run') < thread_lim do sleep 5 end
		    threads << Thread.new do
			    $master_map['builds'][build_name] = TestrayBuild.new(build_name, product_version, $master_map['routines'][job_name], description: build_desc).add_to_parent_routine
		    end
	    end
	    threads.each {|t| t.join}
    else
	    table.rows.each do |job_name, build_name, build_desc, product_version|

			    @hash_response = obj.instance_variable_get(:@hash_response)
		    end
	    end
	    threads.each {|t| t.join}
    end

When(/^I add the following automation results to run "([^\"]*)" in the "([^\"]*)" build using JSON$/) do |run_num, build_name, table|
    result_arr = []
    table.rows.each do |row| # Create request
        case row[2].downcase
            when 'blocked'
                status_val = 4
            when 'failed'
                status_val = 3
            when 'in progress'
                status_val = 1
            when 'passed'
                status_val = 2
            when 'retest'
                status_val = 5
            when 'test fix'
                status_val = 7
            when 'untested'
                status_val = 0
            when ''
                puts 'No status to update with given. Not updating case result status.'
            else
                puts "Incorrect or misspelled status entered. You entered: #{row[2]}"
        end

        request_array = {
              'testrayCaseId' => "#{$master_map['cases'][row[0]].id}",
              'testrayRunId' => "#{$master_map['runs'][build_name][run_num].id}",
              'status' => status_val,
              'comment' => "#{row[3]}",
              'issues' => "#{row[4]}",
              'errors' => "#{row[5]}"
        }
        result_arr.push(request_array)
    end
    TestrayCaseResult.add_bulk_results($master_map['runs'][build_name][run_num], result_arr)

    # Update comment and user for each result
    table.rows.each do |row|
        user_id = get_user_ids(row[1])

        $master_map['runs'][build_name][run_num].results[row[0]].update(200, comment: "#{row[3]}", assigned_user_id: user_id.join(','))
    end
end

When(/^I add the following tasks? using JSON$/) do |table|
    $master_map['tasks'] ||= {}
    table.rows.each do |row|
        task_name = row[0]
        build = row[1]

        case_types = row[2].gsub(', ',',').split(',')
        for i in 0..case_types.length-1
            testray_get(case_types[i], 'case_types')
            case_types[i] = get_hash_response('case_types', case_types[i])
        end

        users = get_user_ids(row[3])

        $master_map['tasks'][task_name] = TestrayTask.new(task_name, $master_map['builds'][build]).add(case_types.join(','), users.join(','))
    end
end

            end
        end
        threads.each {|t| t.join}
    end

When(/^I apply the following filters to the subtasks in the "([^"]*)" task using JSON$/) do |task_name, table|
    uri_params = "?testrayTaskId=#{$master_map['tasks'][task_name].id}" # Initialize base uri_params

    table.rows.each do |row| # Parse each row to determine Filter Field and its parameters, then append formatted filter parameters to uri_params
        filter_type = row[0]
        filter_param = row[1]

        case filter_type.downcase
            when 'subtask name'
                uri_params << "&filterName=#{CGI::escape(filter_param)}"
            when 'errors'
                uri_params << "&filterErrors=#{CGI::escape(filter_param)}"
            when 'assignee'
                if filter_param.downcase == 'unassigned'
                    uri_params << '&filterAssignedUserId=0'
                else
                    user_ids = get_user_ids(filter_param)
                    uri_params << "&filterAssignedUserId=#{user_ids.join(',')}"
                end
            when 'status'
                uri_params << "&filterStatusLabels=#{filter_param.gsub(' ', '')}"
            when 'team'
                json_req('Get', "#{$testray_path}/teams/_#{CGI::escape(filter_param)}.json?testrayProjectId=#{$master_map['tasks'][task_name].parent_build.parent_project_id}", expected_status: 200)
                team_id = @hash_response['data']['testrayTeamId']
                uri_params << "&filterTestrayTeamId=#{team_id}"
            when 'component'
                uri_params << "&filterTestrayComponentName=#{CGI::escape(filter_param)}"
            else
                raise("Improper or unsupported Filter Field given. You entered: #{filter_type}. Accepted Filter Fields: Priority, Component, Case Name, Assignee, Status, Issue")
        end
    end
    json_req('Get', "#{$testray_path}/subtasks.json", {}, uri_param: uri_params, expected_status: 200)
end

                    end
                end
                uri_params << status_vals
            when 'issue'

                    uri_params << '&filterIssuesBlankOnly=on'
                else
                    uri_params << "&filterIssues=#{filter_param}"
                end
            when 'error'

        end
    end
